The paper deals with the problem of image classification using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves evolving the architecture of the network, which falls under the category of neural evolution (cs.NE) and evolutionary computation (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of shortcut connections is a technique commonly used in deep reinforcement learning (cs.SY).
